    "text": "The RepoRescue dataset includes 193 Python repositories and 122 Java repositories that historically passed but fail after modernization.",
    "topic": "RepoRescue dataset composition"
  },
  {
    "text": "Agents are evaluated on their full-patch pass rate within the RepoRescue dataset.",
    "topic": "Agent evaluation metrics"
  },
  {
    "text": "Source-only repair is one of the evaluation criteria for agents in the RepoRescue dataset.",
    "topic": "Agent evaluation criteria"
  },
  {
    "text": "Runtime-enforced blocking of test edits is used as an evaluation method for agents in the RepoRescue dataset.",
    "topic": "Agent evaluation methods"
  },
  {
    "text": "RepoRescue differentiates compatibility rescue from bug repair by focusing on adapting old repositories to modern environments due to ecosystem drift.",
    "topic": "RepoRescue focus on compatibility rescue"
  }
]
